subSection.paragraph:
Campopleginae is one of the most diverse subfamilies of Ichneumonidae ( Hymenoptera ) with about 2,500 valid species worldwide (
Yu et al . 2016
). As koinobiont endoparasitoids of various (mostly lepidopteran) larvae ( Wahl 1993 ), several species of the subfamily are used in biological pest control (e.g., Godfray 1994 ; Sarfaz et al . 2005; Ayalew & Hopkins 2013 ). The Campopleginae fauna of Iran has been extensively studied, resulting mainly faunistic records and important distributional data (e.g., Mohammadi-Khoramabadi & Riedel 2020 ;
Samin et al . 2021
), but also taxonomic results of relevance to the whole Palaearctic diversity of the subfamily (e.g.,
Riedel et al . 2019a
,b;
Vas et al . 2022
).

